     \subsection{Research-track companion}
         Sectors that are useful for continuity but too long or too provisional for a minimal main-canon reading are collected in the companion research-track file of the current edition.  Its contents are versioned with the main canon; no historical filename or fixed contents list is normative.  The integration subsections below retain the in-context interfaces and cross-references, while the companion supplies the extended derivations, diagnostics, and research programmes.  Editorial separation does not reject these sectors; it prevents the core narrative from over-claiming closure.
 
+    \subsection{KAM-caged knot-state stability guard}
+        \label{subsec:canon_kam_caged_knot_guard}
+
+        \paragraph{Status.}
+        \textbf{[CANON/RT INTERFACE].}
+        The canon now distinguishes two mathematically different uses of KAM
+        structure in a vortex-knot programme:
+        \begin{align}
+            \mathrm{KAM\mbox{-}S}
+            &:
+            \text{spatial confinement of vortex lines inside a steady tube},
+            \\
+            \mathrm{KAM\mbox{-}T}
+            &:
+            \text{temporal nonlinear stability of the moving knot shape}.
+            \label{eq:canon_kam_spatial_temporal_split}
+        \end{align}
+        Rigorous steady Euler constructions establish that knotted vortex tubes
+        can contain an elliptic periodic core line, a positive-measure family of
+        invariant tori, and infinitely many periodic vortex lines
+        \cite{KhesinKuksinPeraltaSalas2014,EncisoPeraltaSalas2015}.  This is an
+        orthodox precedent for \(\mathrm{KAM\mbox{-}S}\).  It does not by itself
+        prove that a freely evolving SST carrier retains its geometry under its
+        complete self-induced motion; that stronger question is
+        \(\mathrm{KAM\mbox{-}T}\).
+
+        The research track therefore uses the nearly integrable template
+        \begin{equation}
+            H(\mathbf I,\boldsymbol\theta)
+            =
+            H_0(\mathbf I)
+            +
+            \varepsilon H_1(\mathbf I,\boldsymbol\theta),
+            \label{eq:canon_kam_nearly_integrable_template}
+        \end{equation}
+        only after a relative equilibrium or periodic relative orbit has been
+        identified and its translational, rotational, phase, and
+        reparametrization zero modes have been removed.  Integrability of the
+        local-induction equation through the Hasimoto map supplies a candidate
+        reference layer, while the nonlocal finite-core Biot--Savart correction
+        supplies a candidate perturbation layer
+        \cite{Hasimoto1972,JerrardSeis2017,MarsdenWeinstein1983}:
+        \begin{equation}
+            H_{\rm BS}
+            =
+            H_{\rm LIA}
+            +
+            \varepsilon_{\rm NL} H_{\rm NL}.
+            \label{eq:canon_kam_lia_bs_split}
+        \end{equation}
+        Equation~\eqref{eq:canon_kam_lia_bs_split} is a
+        \textbf{[BRIDGE/RESEARCH]} decomposition, not yet a derived canonical
+        SST action in global action--angle variables.  The effective
+        perturbation size \(\varepsilon_{\rm NL}\) must be measured from the
+        same regularized evolution used in the nonlinear simulation; it may not
+        be declared small solely because \(a_{\rm core}/R\ll1\).
+
+        The admissible promotion order is
+        \begin{align}
+            &\text{certified topology}
+            \longrightarrow
+            \text{relative equilibrium}
+            \longrightarrow
+            \text{reduced Floquet ellipticity}
+            \nonumber\\
+            &\quad\longrightarrow
+            \text{nonlinear normal form and twist}
+            \longrightarrow
+            \text{invariant-torus evidence}
+            \nonumber\\
+            &\quad\longrightarrow
+            \text{computer-assisted KAM certificate}.
+            \label{eq:canon_kam_promotion_ladder}
+        \end{align}
+        Topology alone does not imply any later rung.  A robust multiplier
+        outside the unit circle, a vanishing reduced twist matrix, uncontrolled
+        nonlocal induction, or secular action drift blocks KAM promotion even
+        when the knot type remains unchanged.
+
+        \paragraph{Golden-ratio and spiral discipline.}
+        A golden or noble rotation number may be tested as a
+        \textbf{[HYPOTHESIS]} only by comparing its measured torus-break threshold
+        against preregistered irrational and rational controls.  No golden
+        constant may enter the equilibrium optimizer, mesh, initial-condition
+        selector, or stopping rule.  The open logarithmic spiral
+        \begin{equation}
+            r(\theta)=a e^{b\theta},
+            \qquad
+            b=\frac{2\ln\phi}{\pi},
+            \label{eq:canon_golden_log_spiral_rejected}
+        \end{equation}
+        is \textbf{[REJECTED]} as a closed particle centreline because
+        \(r(\theta+2\pi)=\phi^4r(\theta)\neq r(\theta)\).  Alternative closed
+        modulation geometries are intentionally excluded from the release
+        canon until they pass free-parameter comparison, topology, reach,
+        clearance, and dynamical-selection gates.
